Alternatively, you can use the following wget command to download the Arduino Software (IDE) package directly on the terminal.

At the time of this writing, the current latest version is 1.8.15.

cd /tmp
wget https://downloads.arduino.cc/arduino-1.8.15-linux64.tar.xz

Next, extract the downloaded archive file using the tar command as shown below.

tar -xvf arduino-1.8.15-linux64.tar.xz

Now move into the extracted arduino-1.8.15 directory and run the installation script as root.

cd arduino-1.8.12/
sudo ./install.sh


ثم تنزيل المكتبات عن طريق الاردينو مرفق صور

